
[1]exclamation

   EXCLAMA'TION, n. Outcry; noisy talk; clamor; as exclamations against
   abuses in government.

   1. Vehement vociferation.

   Thus will I drown your exclamations.

   2. Emphatical utterance; a vehement extension or elevation of voice;
   ecphonesis; as, O dismal night!

   3. A note by which emphatical utterance or outcry is marked: thus!

   4. In grammar, a word expressing outcry; an interjection; a word
   expressing some passion, as wonder, fear or grief.
